-- Usmanov to Add Scartel Into His Telecom Holding, Vedomosti Says
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-04-26T06:04:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-26/usmanov-to-add-scartel-into-his-telecom-holding-vedomosti-says.html
Russian billionaire Alisher Usmanov
plans to form a joint telecommunications holding with
shareholders of Scartel broadband internet provider, which
operates under the Yota brandname,  Vedomosti  reported.  The company will unite 100 percent shares of Scartel and
Usmanov’s 50 percent stake in cell-phone operator OAO Megafon,
the Moscow-based newspaper said citing Ivan Streshinsky, head of
Usmanov’s telecommunication business. Scartel is valued at $1
billion for the deal, according to Vedomosti.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
